txn_fields.name: FirstValidTime
txn_fields.note: Causes program to fail; reserved for future use

txn_fields.name: AssetSender
txn_fields.note: 32 byte address. Causes clawback of all value of asset from AssetSender if Sender is the Clawback address of the asset.

txn_fields.name: GroupIndex
txn_fields.note: Position of this transaction within an atomic transaction group. A stand-alone transaction is implicitly element 0 in a group of 1

txn_fields.name: TxID
txn_fields.note: The computed ID for this transaction. 32 bytes.

txn_fields.name: OnCompletion
txn_fields.note: ApplicationCall transaction on completion action. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: ApplicationArgs
txn_fields.note: Arguments passed to the application in the ApplicationCall transaction. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: Accounts
txn_fields.note: Accounts listed in the ApplicationCall transaction. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: ConfigAsset
txn_fields.note: Asset ID in asset config transaction. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: ConfigAssetTotal
txn_fields.note: Total number of units of this asset created. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: ConfigAssetDecimals
txn_fields.note: Number of digits to display after the decimal place when displaying the asset. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: ConfigAssetDefaultFrozen
txn_fields.note: Whether the asset's slots are frozen by default or not, 0 or 1. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: ConfigAssetUnitName
txn_fields.note: Unit name of the asset. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: ConfigAssetMetadataHash
txn_fields.note: 32 byte commitment to some unspecified asset metadata. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: FreezeAsset
txn_fields.note: Asset ID being frozen or un-frozen. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: FreezeAssetAccount
txn_fields.note: 32 byte address of the account whose asset slot is being frozen or un-frozen. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: FreezeAssetFrozen
txn_fields.note: The new frozen value, 0 or 1. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

txn_fields.name: Assets
txn_fields.note: Foreign Assets listed in the ApplicationCall transaction. LogicSigVersion >= 3.

txn_fields.name: Applications
txn_fields.note: Foreign Apps listed in the ApplicationCall transaction. LogicSigVersion >= 3.

txn_fields.name: GlobalNumUint
txn_fields.note: Number of global state integers in ApplicationCall. LogicSigVersion >= 3.

txn_fields.name: GlobalNumByteSlice
txn_fields.note: Number of global state byteslices in ApplicationCall. LogicSigVersion >= 3.

txn_fields.name: LocalNumUint
txn_fields.note: Number of local state integers in ApplicationCall. LogicSigVersion >= 3.

txn_fields.name: LocalNumByteSlice
txn_fields.note: Number of local state byteslices in ApplicationCall. LogicSigVersion >= 3.

txn_fields.name: ExtraProgramPages
txn_fields.note: Number of additional pages for each of the application's approval and clear state programs. An ExtraProgramPages of 1 means 2048 more total bytes, or 1024 for each program. LogicSigVersion >= 4.

txn_fields.name: Nonparticipation
txn_fields.note: Marks an account nonparticipating for rewards. LogicSigVersion >= 5.

txn_fields.name: Logs
txn_fields.note: Log messages emitted by an application call (itxn only). LogicSigVersion >= 5.

txn_fields.name: CreatedAssetID
txn_fields.note: Asset ID allocated by the creation of an ASA (itxn only). LogicSigVersion >= 5.

txn_fields.name: CreatedApplicationID
txn_fields.note: ApplicationID allocated by the creation of an application (itxn only). LogicSigVersion >= 5.

oncomplete.name: NoOp
oncomplete.desc: Only execute the ApprovalProgram associated with this application ID, with no additional effects.

oncomplete.name: OptIn
oncomplete.desc: Before executing the ApprovalProgram, allocate local state for this application into the sender's account data.

oncomplete.name: CloseOut
oncomplete.desc: After executing the ApprovalProgram, clear any local state for this application out of the sender's account data.

oncomplete.name: ClearState
oncomplete.desc: Don't execute the ApprovalProgram, and instead execute the ClearStateProgram (which may not reject this transaction). Additionally, clear any local state for this application out of the sender's account data as in CloseOutOC.

oncomplete.name: UpdateApplication
oncomplete.desc: After executing the ApprovalProgram, replace the ApprovalProgram and ClearStateProgram associated with this application ID with the programs specified in this transaction.

oncomplete.name: DeleteApplication
oncomplete.desc: After executing the ApprovalProgram, delete the application parameters from the account data of the application's creator.

global_fields.name: ZeroAddress
global_fields.note: 32 byte address of all zero bytes

global_fields.name: GroupSize
global_fields.note: Number of transactions in this atomic transaction group. At least 1

global_fields.name: LatestTimestamp
global_fields.note: Last confirmed block UNIX timestamp. Fails if negative. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

global_fields.name: CurrentApplicationID
global_fields.note: ID of current application executing. Fails if no such application is executing. LogicSigVersion >= 2.

global_fields.name: CreatorAddress
global_fields.note: Address of the creator of the current application. Fails if no such application is executing. LogicSigVersion >= 3.

asset_holding_get_fields.name: AssetBalance
asset_holding_get_fields.note: Amount of the asset unit held by this account

asset_holding_get_fields.name: AssetFrozen
asset_holding_get_fields.note: Is the asset frozen or not

asset_params_get_fields.name: AssetTotal
asset_params_get_fields.note: Total number of units of this asset

asset_params_get_fields.name: AssetURL
asset_params_get_fields.note: URL with additional info about the asset
